author: @lisafiets
text:
There were Naver articles published about SEVENTEEN on how what makes them standout from the industry is that they never changed: they still perform as if they're rookies, with just as much drive and passion. Too often senior artists become complacent over time because of their status and popularity, but SEVENTEEN is different in that their performance level has remained consistent throughout their entire career, AND constantly improving and being fine-tuned.They declare it themselves quite often too, that they hope they will never lose that "rookie mindset", and it really does show in everything they do: from their humility, their welcoming openness to their fellow Kpop idols of all generations, their active involvement in all aspects of their career, the way they practice and perform as hard as if they're just about to debut next month.
Their professionalism and discipline in their craft, coupled with the sincerity of their artistry and the joyful energy they have as a group, shows all the more starkly here in their Rock With You choreography. The passion and love for what they doâ€”and their undying commitment to their Caratsâ€”is exactly what this performance is all about.

author: @vindicatedtruth
text:
A computer algorithm once concluded that SEVENTEEN is the most synchronized idol group in the industry (even across generations), with almost a 96% accuracy, which is as humanly close to perfection as possible.

Synchronization is no joke especially for a group of 13 members, because that's thirteen times the chance of having mistakes, and yet there's no other group currently in the industry who executes that knife-life synchronization the way they do. Once you get to observe for yourself the "SEVENTEEN STANDARD" in performing, you'll start to view other performances by other idols by that standard, and realise just how almost impossibly high SEVENTEEN has set it for the industry to follow. 

And yet what makes the dance practice behind videos such those on INSIDE SEVENTEEN all the more important to reveal is because that standard of near-perfection doesn't come easy. It comes with the absolute discipline in honing even the littlest details in their choreographyâ€”down to the angle of their arms and the timing of their gesturesâ€”and as they clearly demonstrate in those behind-the-scenes: practicing even to the point of absolute exhaustion.

It's the kind of reverence and respect that only SEVENTEEN can inspire, because even after seven years in the industry, and ten years practicing together since pre-debut, they have never let themselves be complacent in their craft.

SEVENTEEN is the standard of performance because they set it so highly, first and foremost, for THEMSELVES.

author: @eejoy7566
text:
the audio tracks of the original song and the 007 version is different, whether if the bass was enhanced, or how you can hear their voices better.
some examples (there are probably a lot more):
0:44 jeonghan vocals + backing vocals are more crisp(?)
0:56 guitars much clearer than original; the ohhhh~ is also much clearer
1:02 backing vocals in seungcheol's part are clearer
1:08 claps/percussion lowered to emphasise bass
1:19 chorus vocals much clearer due to harmonies not being there (only melody); guitar seems clearer 
1:42 during dino's line, 3 beats play in the back leading into the 2nd verse, while in the original there's only 1 beat
1:45 wonwoo's vocals much clearer; the 'mwodeun' part that was reverb in the original becomes backing vocals in 007 ver
1:55 percussion much clearer than the guitar (opposite of mingyu's prechorus)
2:06 claps/percussion lowered again to emphasise bass
2:16 guitar riff much clearer
2:18 chorus vocals much clearer due to harmonies not being there again (only melody); guitar seems clearer 
2:53 personally i think the instrumental here was lowered for seungcheol vocals
3:03 harmonies on woozi's lines removed; easily can hear the lower octave
3:10 the moment jun kicks, you can hear a 'hey' at the back (clearer on the right earphone) which is also in the original, but barely audible
3:15 from here onwards, all vocal lines have different quality than the original, even though it's the same vocal recordings

i think this version of the song was separately mixed just for the 007 theme. i'll edit the comment and add changes i notice later on. seventeen went out of their way to mix their song for halloween and these changes were so exciting to find. soty for sure

author: @vindicatedtruth
text:
There were Naver articles published about SEVENTEEN on how what makes them standout from the industry is that they never changed: they still perform as if they're rookies, with just as much drive and passion. Too often senior artists become complacent over time because of their status and popularity, but SEVENTEEN is different in that their performance level has remained consistent throughout their entire career, AND constantly improving and being fine-tuned.

They declare it themselves quite often too, that they hope they will never lose that "rookie mindset", and it really does show in everything they do: from their humility, their welcoming openness to their fellow Kpop idols of all generations, their active involvement in all aspects of their career, the way they practice and perform as hard as if they're just about to debut next month.

Their professionalism and discipline in their craft, coupled with the sincerity of their artistry and the joyful energy they have as a group, shows all the more starkly here in their Rock With You choreography. The passion and love for what they doâ€”and their undying commitment to their Caratsâ€”is exactly what this performance is all about.

text:
OK, this might be long, but hear me out:
Seventeen as Professional Assassins
Project Innocence - Seemingly average men in average jobs. Their specialty? Death? No. They will make you wish you were dead. You will live. However, they will destroy your career, your family, your mind-- your life. 
Codename: CHARZMA
The embodiment of "If looks could kill," and they will. Seeing one is akin to seeing an omen of death. Violent, painless, gun, knife, or a boomerang- the method or weapon matters not. The outcome is inescapable, inevitable. 
Enigma
Not the official name. They have no sobriquet. One day, they're robbing the crown jewels. Next, holding tycoons hostage. Then, a sudden bloody rampage. They are ENIGMA. 

If you read until here, which unit is which??
